						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1483, Dundubhi, Nija-Śrāvaṇa, śu. 10</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1562 August 9, Sunday</hi> (not verifiable), in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Sadāśivarāya.</hi> It records that <hi rend="bold">Pedapa,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Gājulla-Nāgayya</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">Adhikāri</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Nagarehāḷ</hi> fixed the <hi rend="italic">dasavandha</hi> payment on a canal at Nagarehāḷ and granted <hi rend="italic">mānya</hi> lands to <hi rend="italic">Sēnabōva</hi> <hi rend="bold">Timmarasa,</hi> the <hi rend="italic">Gauḍa, Taḷāra</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Jōyisa.</hi></p>						

						<p>First Face.</p>						

						</summary>
